description: Intel CEO Lip-Bu Tan has initiated a hands-on leadership policy, personally reviewing and approving major chip designs before tape-out. The policy is part of a broader strategy to streamline operations and strengthen Intel's product roadmap amid pressure from competitors like TSMC.

description: Ken Dryden, the Montreal Canadiens' legendary goalie, has died at 78 after battling cancer. A Hockey Hall of Famer, he led the Canadiens to six Stanley Cups in the 1970s. description: Crime Branch have arrested Ashwin Kumar Supra from Noida for allegedly sending bomb threat messages to the Mumbai Traffic Police's WhatsApp helpline. description: A recent study reveals that smoking not only elevates the risk of pancreatic cancer but also actively promotes tumor growth by suppressing the body's immune defenses. This double-edged effect accelerates tumor development while simultaneously weakening the immune system's ability to fight the disease. For high-risk individuals, proactive screening and quitting smoking are crucial steps.

description: A Canadian Department of Finance report reveals that Khalistani extremist groups, along with Hamas and Hezbollah, receive financial support from Canada. description: Tarzan Sheikh, a migrant worker from Katwa, alleged he was assaulted in Odisha for being a "Bengali-speaking Bangladeshi."
